content: How do I join the Slack. When I keep clicking the link, it asks me to sign in, then when I do, it says "Create Account", but I already have one
Hi 9+10 you should be able to go to Slack (on mobile is bottom of screen) and click "add workplace" then "sign into another workplace" or "join another workplace"
well I click that and then I get this
Is slack being used for any of the teams anymore? Calls and Text are both fully migrated over to the Discord office. When did you receive this Slack channel <@442763913348513793> ?
today during the phonebanking session for Anytime Calling
Did you sign in with the same email that you used for your other Slack accounts?
is your invite using the same email as your Slack login?
the only other Slack account I have is for work
Yes, I know that [Spanish phonebankers](https://events.democrats.org/event/647512/) are still on Slack.
I'm using a different email which i signed in using
What is the name to look up to join slack?
log out of your work Slack, then use the link in the email.

I cannot find the link
Can you drop it here?
it is given to you during the phonebanking session for Anytime Calling
I am a facilitator of the phone banking and never saw it???
https://txt.democrats.org/SlackJoin here's the link
on my Desktop I just keep getting this
Clear your browsing history and try the link again.
I hit Create Account then nothing happens
Thank you, I am in!
should look like this. Can you try different browser?
yeah I see that, then I continue with google, and then the ss I sent comes up
<@442763913348513793> I just took down your image so your email address wasn't up for all to see... but we saw it... just didn't want you to worry ðŸ™‚
When I hit 'continue with Google' and chose an email address, it sent me an authentication code. Whaat happens when you choose "continue with email" and use your personal email address?
I was using my personal email address but I'll try continue with email
the continue with email worked ðŸ™Œ
that was so annoying
If you still need to use Slack for your, you can have Slack connected to your work email in Chrome and also connected with your personal email in Firefox, or any two different browsers.
100% I think I had to authenticate 6 times just to help you troubleshoot... we're super secure. Thanks, Slack!
